h1(Client API: Complete Reference)
h3(Connect to OBLIT servers and send/receive data with ease.)

The <code>Client</code> class provides a lightweight, event-driven TCP client for connecting to OBLIT servers. It handles all the low-level protocol details, including stream reassembly and automatic type detection.

![info](The Client API is intentionally simple. Just connect, send, and receive. OBLIT handles the rest automatically.)!++

!(line)

h2(ğŸ“¦ Constructor)

h3(<code>new Client(address)</code>)

Creates a new client instance. The client does **not** connect until you call <code>cn()</code>.

<div class="table-wrapper"><table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>address</code></td><td><code>String</code></td><td>Yes</td><td>Server address in format <code>'HOST:PORT'</code> (e.g., <code>'127.0.0.1:8080'</code>)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<h3(Examples)

![code](const { Client } = require('oblit');

// Connect to localhost
const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:3000');

// Connect to remote server
const remoteClient = new Client('example.com:8080');

// Connect with default port (3000)
const defaultClient = new Client('192.168.1.100:3000');)!++//

<div style="background:var(--box-info-bg); padding:15px; border-radius:8px; margin:15px 0; border-left:4px solid var(--primary);">
<strong>Address Format:</strong><br><br>
â€¢ <code>HOST</code> can be an IP address (<code>192.168.1.1</code>) or domain name (<code>example.com</code>)<br>
â€¢ <code>PORT</code> must be a number between 1 and 65535<br>
â€¢ Format is always <code>'HOST:PORT'</code> with a colon separator
</div>

!(line)

h2(âš™ï¸ Methods)

h3(<code>client.cn([callback])</code>)

Establishes a TCP connection to the server. This is an alias for <code>connect()</code>.

<div class="table-wrapper"><table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>callback</code></td><td><code>Function</code></td><td>No</td><td>Called once when connection is successfully established. Receives no arguments.</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<h3(Examples)

![code](const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:8080');

// Connect with callback
client.cn(() => {
    console.log('âœ… Connected to server!');
    // Send initial message
    client.snd('Hello from client!');
});

// Connect without callback
client.cn();

// Or use the 'ready' event
client.on('ready', () => {
    console.log('Server connection established');
});
client.cn();)!++//

h3(<code>client.snd(message)</code>)

Sends a message to the server. The data type is automatically detected and packed appropriately.

<div class="table-wrapper"><table><thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>message</code></td><td><code>String | Object | Buffer</code></td><td>Yes</td><td>The data to send. Type is auto-detected: Stringâ†’OP.TXT, Objectâ†’OP.JSON, Bufferâ†’OP.RAW</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<h3(Examples)

![code](const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:8080');
client.cn(() => {
    // Send text message
    client.snd('Hello Server!');

    // Send JSON object
    client.snd({ type: 'login', username: 'player1', score: 100 });

    // Send binary data (for games, sensor data, etc.)
    const positionData = Buffer.alloc(6);
    positionData.writeUInt16BE(42, 0);  // Player ID
    positionData.writeUInt16BE(100, 2); // X coordinate
    positionData.writeUInt16BE(200, 4); // Y coordinate
    client.snd(positionData);

    // Send periodically
    setInterval(() => {
        client.snd({ type: 'heartbeat', timestamp: Date.now() });
    }, 5000);
});)!++//

<div style="background:var(--box-tip-bg); padding:15px; border-radius:8px; margin:15px 0; border-left:4px solid #22c55e;">
<strong>ğŸ’¡ Tip:</strong> For high-frequency data (like player positions in games), use Buffer/RAW mode for maximum performance. See the **[Game Tutorial](#!/tut_game)** for examples.
</div>

!(line)

h2(ğŸ“¡ Events)

h3(<code>'ready'</code> Event)

Emitted when the connection to the server is successfully established.

![code](const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:8080');

client.on('ready', () => {
    console.log('Connected and ready to send data!');
    client.snd('First message');
});

client.cn();)!++//

h3(<code>'data'</code> Event)

Emitted whenever a complete packet is received from the server.

<div class="table-wrapper"><table><thead><tr><th>Event Name</th><th>Callback Arguments</th><th>When Emitted</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>'data'</code></td><td><code>(message)</code></td><td>When a complete packet arrives from the server</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

<h3(Examples)

![code](const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:8080');

client.on('data', (message) => {
    // Handle different message types
    if (typeof message === 'string') {
        console.log('Text message:', message);
    } else if (typeof message === 'object' && !Buffer.isBuffer(message)) {
        console.log('JSON message:', message);
        if (message.type === 'chat') {
            console.log(`${message.user}: ${message.text}`);
        }
    } else if (Buffer.isBuffer(message)) {
        console.log('Binary data received:', message);
        // Unpack binary data
        const playerId = message.readUInt16BE(0);
        const x = message.readUInt16BE(2);
        // ... process binary data
    }
});

client.cn();)!++//

h3(<code>'close'</code> Event)

Emitted when the connection to the server is closed.

![code](const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:8080');

client.on('close', () => {
    console.log('Connection closed. Attempting reconnect...');
    // Implement reconnection logic here
    setTimeout(() => client.cn(), 1000);
});

client.cn();)!++//

h3(<code>'error'</code> Event)

Emitted when a connection error occurs.

![code](const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:8080');

client.on('error', (error) => {
    console.error('Connection error:', error.message);

    if (error.code === 'ECONNREFUSED') {
        console.log('Server is not running or unreachable');
    } else if (error.code === 'ETIMEDOUT') {
        console.log('Connection timeout');
    }
});

client.cn();)!++//

!(line)

h2(ğŸ’¡ Complete Example)

Here's a complete, production-ready client example:

![code](const { Client } = require('oblit');

const client = new Client('127.0.0.1:8080');

// Handle connection ready
client.on('ready', () => {
    console.log('âœ… Connected to server');

    // Send login message
    client.snd({ type: 'login', username: 'player1' });
});

// Handle incoming messages
client.on('data', (message) => {
    if (typeof message === 'object') {
        switch (message.type) {
            case 'welcome':
                console.log('Server says:', message.text);
                break;
            case 'chat':
                console.log(`[${message.user}] ${message.text}`);
                break;
            case 'game_update':
                // Process game state update
                updateGameState(message.data);
                break;
        }
    }
});

// Handle connection close
client.on('close', () => {
    console.log('âŒ Connection lost. Reconnecting...');
    setTimeout(() => client.cn(), 2000);
});

// Handle errors
client.on('error', (error) => {
    console.error('Connection error:', error.message);
});

// Connect
client.cn();)!++//

![tip](Want to see more examples? Check out the **[Chat Tutorial](#!/tut_chat)** and **[Game Server Tutorial](#!/tut_game)** for complete, working applications.)!++

